course_name: Professionalism in Academic Medicine and Health
description: Acquisition and evaluation of interpersonal and communication skills and professionalism including ethics and cultural competence; within the context of health care disparities and health initiatives.

course_name: Fieldwork: Designing Innovations for the Health Professions
description: Individual projects designing curricular or other innovations for the home program as an application of Year 1 concepts and as part of the capstone experience. Graded CR/NC.

course_name: Supporting the Educational Enterprise in Academic Medicine
description: Explores support functions in academic medical centers and health professions schools; financial, scientific, educational, faculty and student affairs departments, and offices of medical education.

course_name: Faculty Development for Health Sciences Faculty Educators
description: Role of faculty development programs in health professions schools; tools for delivering effective continuing education and faculty development; models for mentoring clinical faculty.

course_name: Capstone Portfolio for the Master of Academic Medicine
description: Role of portfolios for teachers and learners; develop a personal capstone portfolio that represents each learners accomplishment of the core competencies of the MACM program.
